AUS.leaveHelp:
'Leave Available' is your up to date annual leave balance and may differ from your annual leave entitlement in PeopleSoft.

'Leave Booked' includes all annual leave requests submitted for future dates.

Annual Leave requests for dates within the current pay period will appear in 'Leave Booked' until approved. When approved it will stop appearing in 'Leave Booked' and will be deducted from 'Leave Available' within 24 hours.
AUS.payHelp:
'Last Pay' is your most recent pay.

'Next Pay' is the subsequent pay date following the last pay.

ALM.title: Airport lounge m'ship
ALM.help: Reimbursement requires manager approval and therefore payment will apply in the next available pay period post manager approval.

CARP.title: Car parking
CARP.help: Each location has a fixed rate that is calculated automatically once the location is selected.

CGIV.title: Community Giving
CGIV.help: Also referred to as Workplace Giving. Payments can either be serviced as an on-going deduction or can be made as a once off donation.

HELP REIM.title: HELP fee reimb No GST
HELP REIM.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

STUDY NOGST.title: Study reimb No GST
STUDY NOGST.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

STUDY GST.title: Study reimb GST
STUDY GST.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

EXTENDED 030.title: Ext hrs load 0.30
EXTENDED 030.help: Applicable for contracted hours worked commencing before 7.00 am and after 7.00 pm - Monday to Friday.

EXTENDED 050.title: Ext hrs load 0.50
EXTENDED 050.help: Applicable for contracted hours worked commencing from 8.00 am to 4.00 pm on Saturday. This loading may be used for penalty rates on public holidays as applicable.

EXTENDED 100.title: Ext hrs load 1.00
EXTENDED 100.help: Applicable for contracted hours worked commencing before 8.00 am and after 4.00 p.m. on Saturdays, Sundays and all public holidays.

INC BNK CAR.title: Bank car incdtl
INC BNK CAR.help: Reimbursement of Tool Of Trade costs paid by employee. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

INC CAR PRK.title: Car park incdtl FBT
INC CAR PRK.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

OT 100.title: Overtime load 1.00
OT 100.help: Applicable for single time payments i.e. travelling time, etc.

OT 125.title: Overtime load 1.25
OT 125.help: 25% PAC (Pay Above Contract) loading for part timers who work outside contracted hours up to 152 hours per 4 weekly cycle.

OT 150.title: Overtime load 1.50
OT 150.help: Applicable for the first 12 hours over 152/160 per 4 weekly cycle.   Enter the date/s or the 4 weekly cycle date range in the comments section.

OT 200.title: Overtime load 2.00
OT 200.help: Applicable for working more than 12 hours over 152/160 per 4 weekly cycle or overtime on a Saturday or Sunday. Enter the date/s or the 4 weekly cycle date range in the comments section.

CHLDCARE COS.title: Childcare cost FBT
CHLDCARE COS.help: Reimbursement of additional child care costs, when a part-time employee attends bank requested training sessions or staff meetings when they are not scheduled to work. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

ENTMT MEAL.title: Entmt - meals
ENTMT MEAL.help: Meals for clients / potential clients or guests of ANZ. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

ENTMT NOMEAL.title: Entmt - non meals FBT
ENTMT NOMEAL.help: Movie, theatre tickets, drinks etc for clients or potential clients. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

INC EXPENSES.title: Incidental expenses
INC EXPENSES.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

INT AGN INC.title: Intl assignee incidentals
INT AGN INC.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

INT TFR UTIL.title: Intl tfr utilities FBT
INT TFR UTIL.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

RELOC ED.title: Educ/Board fees FBT
RELOC ED.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

RELOC BS NG.title: Home buy/sell loss
RELOC BS NG.help: Reimbursement of stamp duty costs for eligible employees who sell/buy their home (principal place of residence).

RELOC DOM LV.title: Domestic (living)
RELOC DOM LV.help: A reimbursement of meals and laundry expenses while staying in transit accommodation. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

RELOC DOM TR.title: Domestic (travel)
RELOC DOM TR.help: Reimbursement of taxi and train fares for pre-appointment visit and/or relocation, includes airfares.

SHFTLD AFT.title: Shift Ld afternoon
SHFTLD AFT.help: Loading of 15% for starting a shift at or after 11.00am but before 7.00pm.

SHFTLD MORN.title: Shift Ld morning
SHFTLD MORN.help: Loading of 12.5% for starting a shift at or after 4.00am but before 7.00am.

SHFTLD NGHT.title: Shift Ld night
SHFTLD NGHT.help: Loading of 27.5% for starting a shift at or after 7.00pm but before 4.00am the next day.

SHFTLD WKND.title: Shift Ld wknd/ph
SHFTLD WKND.help: Loading of 100% applies when more than half of an employees shift falls on a Saturday, Sunday, or Public Holiday.

DOM TRAVEL.title: Domestic allowance
DOM TRAVEL.help: This non-taxed allowance covers meal costs and miscellaneous costs such as telephone and dry cleaning while travelling domestically on ANZ business.  Domestic travel includes New Zealand.

TRAV VACC.title: Med costs & trav vacc FBT
TRAV VACC.help: Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

TRV FARES.title: Excess fare FBT
TRV FARES.help: Reimbursement for travelling costs following ANZ initiated relocations. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

TRAV EXP MED.title: Exp remote medic FBT
TRAV EXP MED.help: Travel expenses for fares for an employee and their dependants where they are working at a country branch due to an ANZ-initiated relocation and need to travel more than 200 km to obtain treatment. Evidence is required in the form of receipts.

PRTX VOL SUP.title: Pre tax Vol Super
PRTX VOL SUP.help: Enter the percentage or dollar amount of additional contributions you wish to make before tax.

PSTX VOL SUP.title: Post tax Vol Super
PSTX VOL SUP.help: Enter the percentage or dollar amount of additional contributions you wish to make after tax.

NZL.leaveHelp:
Leave Available differs from the Annual leave entitlement displayed in PeopleSoft.

In the app, we have removed any future booked annual leave so what you see is what you have available right now.

The Leave Booked balance reflects the total of all your approved future leave requests.
NZL.payHelp:
'Last Pay' is your most recent pay.

'Next Pay' is the subsequent pay date following the last pay.

EXP REIMBRS.title: Expense reimburs
EXP REIMBRS.help: Bank Business, Operating Costs, Additional Staff Expenses, General Stationery, Printing Costs.

MEDICAL EXP.title: Medical expenses
MEDICAL EXP.help: This does not include work or non-work related injuries.

CHILD CARE.title: Childcare contribution
CHILD CARE.help: An allowance paid as a result of having to work additional hours (overtime) which results in extra childcare costs.

DOM DLY ALW.title: Domestic daily allownce
DOM DLY ALW.help: Reimbursement for expenses incurred while on temporary duties away from home.

KM REIMB.title: KM reimbursement
KM REIMB.help: If the use of a private vehicle for ANZ business has been approved, you may be paid a reimbursement for kilometres travelled at the rate published by Inland Revenue Department.

PER DIEM.title: Per diem out of pocket exp

ALT HOL ACR.title: Accrue alt hol (hrs)
ALT HOL ACR.help: To receive a payment at normal hourly rate for working additional hours.

ADD HRS X1.title: Add. hours at time one
ADD HRS X1.help: Number of hours worked on a public holiday. Enter the date of the public holiday as "Date Worked"
